{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/background-information/definition/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"ec87042d-84e0-5a22-97eb-f9c346e5f3de","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 39dd07de-2a20-4546-beaf-0a0f5c0d6833 --><h2>What is it?</h2><!-- end field 39dd07de-2a20-4546-beaf-0a0f5c0d6833 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 34f23671-f328-4b7c-a82c-4ab41630cc00 --><!-- begin field d373e0e2-9e57-442d-ae59-2f56c9b36132 --><ul><li><strong>Food allergy describes an adverse immune-mediated response, which occurs when a person is exposed to specific food allergen(s),</strong> usually by ingestion and more rarely by inhalation or skin contact [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Boyce, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Burks, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Turnbull, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">NICE, 2018</a>].</li><li><strong>Cow's milk allergy is a reproducible immune-mediated allergic response to one or more proteins in cow's milk </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Fiocchi et al, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Ludman et al, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Luyt et al, 2014</a>]<strong>.</strong><ul><li>Milk contains casein and whey fractions made up of about 20 potentially sensitizing proteins, which a person can react to.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Cow's milk allergy can be classified</strong> according to the underlying immune mechanism and timing of symptoms [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Fiocchi et al, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Koletzko et al, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Burks, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Ludman et al, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Caffarelli et al, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Luyt et al, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">NICE, 2018</a>]:<ul><li>Immunoglobulin (Ig)E-mediated food allergy follows exposure and sensitization to trigger food allergen(s) with the development of serum-specific IgE antibody. It produces immediate and consistently reproducible symptoms which may affect multiple organs systems. Reactions typically occur up to 2 hours after cow's milk protein ingestion, usually within 20–30 minutes [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Fiocchi et al, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Venter, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Fox, 2019</a>].</li><li>Non-IgE-mediated food allergy involves a cell-mediated mechanism and reactions are typically delayed. They usually manifest between 2 and 72 hours after cow's milk ingestion [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Venter, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Fox, 2019</a>].</li><li>Mixed IgE and non-IgE allergic reactions involve a mixture of both IgE and non-IgE responses and are typically delayed.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Food sensitization</strong> describes the production of serum-specific IgE to food allergens without the clinical symptoms of an allergic reaction on food exposure [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Burks, 2012</a>].</li><li><strong>Food intolerances</strong> are non-immune adverse reactions to foods and/or food additives which are distinct from food allergy [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Boyce, 2010</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Burks, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Turnbull, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">NICE, 2018</a>].<ul><li>They often present non-specifically with gastrointestinal symptoms, headache, fatigue, and musculoskeletal symptoms. Typically, there is a delay in symptom onset and a prolonged symptomatic phase.</li><li>The exact cause is unknown, but they may be due to enzyme deficiencies or pharmacological reactions to chemicals.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field d373e0e2-9e57-442d-ae59-2f56c9b36132 --><!-- end item 34f23671-f328-4b7c-a82c-4ab41630cc00 -->","topic":{"id":"a5282e12-9e0e-5a93-bf1e-c47cb44993b6","topicId":"055e8853-0668-4ee8-bef5-d86e8a39b416","topicName":"Cow's milk allergy in children","slug":"cows-milk-allergy-in-children","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2019","chapters":[{"id":"e95ad3f8-8ddd-57bd-8fe1-a01a59402ca1","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"fceefe8b-f1a1-54cb-add7-5660134a61f9","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ff117841-0d0c-5d1f-ad22-a2d8db741006","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"0a17cde7-a3cc-580f-a5ec-e74a03694b87","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"e8251ee6-b8da-567a-b543-5efa4c24f074","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"5cd1ea49-3964-5480-beb5-1208ab83ecb4","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"6737a350-b49d-5d33-a999-d2a5f41c7f48","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"bb1f8ca2-c855-56ee-bc57-4b1b77c9a276","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"296bbdac-c210-5305-8b31-aabc917df09f","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"5c4984e6-3f82-5632-9d43-2766ecbdec62","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"52bb5ec1-cd13-5a6e-a889-5e1d7a9ffcf6","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"92a5493f-38a6-5d89-a3e6-bcf0d7bfa1d6","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"8bb88e63-0cf4-5025-8dd3-1041e3b9d9ea","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"ec87042d-84e0-5a22-97eb-f9c346e5f3de","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"62433689-0bf5-54f1-a4c2-61d6274cdd19","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"99c10d89-9bd7-5a68-ba37-37973a5b10d4","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"8ef82df6-42bc-5a14-9b57-254620